So am I...but what she wrote still seems to say otherwise at its face value.  You can reason out that she meant to say that in, say, 1920, usage of it be their "centurial" teens might alarm a parent who was born before the dawn of that century, but it's not the prima facie meaning of what Sam wrote.

And that was my point.

@Henry Su 

