@Min 

Those words seem lyrical and beautiful to you because to us they are archaic and are found in literature from a much earlier time . Back then, they were just ordinary words that no one gave a second thought to. 

In 2500, they will look back upon our present language and marvel that we called it “Modern English.”

@Min 

I heartily agree.  
The New Oxford Annotated Bible can be helpful with the meaning of thornier passages, but what it affords in clarity leaves little to no beauty of the King James translation...  The light shineth in the darkness....

@Andrzej 

